<div id="about">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="small-8 small-centered medium-uncentered medium-4 columns about">
			<%= image_tag('profile_picture.png', id: "profile_picture", alt: 'Ryan O\'Connor') %>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<div class="medium-pull-3 columns">
				<h2 id="about_header" class="about text-center">About Me</h2>
			</div>

			<p class="about_text">
				Hi, my name is Ryan O'Connor and I am currently in my 4th year of software engineering at the University of Ottawa. I was first introduced to coding during my Visual Basic programming class back in high school. Ever since then I haven't looked back. After discovering how rewarding it is to solve problems using code, I knew that's what I wanted to do for the rest of my life.
			</p>
			<p class="about_text">
				I am currently VP Academic of the <%= link_to "Software Engineering Student Association", "http://uottawa-sesa.ca" %> where I help organize weekly Ruby on Rails tutorials, study sessions, and coding events for students. When I'm taking a break from programming and helping others, I like to go skating, snowmobiling, or enjoying my time out on the water.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="education">
	<div class="subtitle">
		<div class="row">
			<h2 class="text-center">Education</h2>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">University of Ottawa</h3>
			<p class="date">September 2012 - Current</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>BASc in Software Engineering</strong>
			<p>
				My studies at the University of Ottawa have allowed me to develop strong design skills by using requirements engineering techniques, analysis level diagrams, and design level diagrams. I've also learned how to translate requirements and diagrams into quality software. Java has been used as the main programming language for learning, however I've also had the opportunity to use HTML, CSS, SQL, and Ruby.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="experience">
	<div class="subtitle">
		<div class="row">
			<h2 class="text-center">Experience</h2>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">BiteSite</h3>
			<p class="date">May 2015 - Current</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>Junior Software Developer</strong>
			<p>
				<%= link_to 'BiteSite', 'http://bitesite.ca' %> is a small software development firm based out of Ottawa, Ontario where we develop full stack web applications. While working at BiteSite, I've developed a strong understanding of Ruby on Rails, RSpec through TDD, Git, and a basic understanding of JavaScript. At BiteSite, I had the opportunity to build software both independently, and with a team using agile processes.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row experience">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">Bell Canada</h3>
			<p class="date">June 2014 - August 2014</p>
			<p class="date">May 2015 - August 2015</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>VoIP Manager - Service Assurance and Development</strong>
			<p>
				At Bell Canada I provided quality assurance for Bell's VoIP platform. I helped customers with validation testing and verified that their results were as expected by analyzing SIP traces using Wireshark. I was involved with testing for new platform releases and helped with diagnosing system failures. During my time working at Bell Canada I implemented call forwarding on FreeSwitch for internal release testing.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row experience">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">SigmaPoint Technologies</h3>
			<p class="date">May 2013 - August 2013</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>Kontron Mechanic</strong>
			<p>
				SigmaPoint Technologies is an electronics manufacturer where I worked as a Kontron mechanic. I assembled, diagnosed, and repaired CompactPCI boards and server boards. I worked under the Toyota Production System, used to provide quality products in a fast and efficient manner while reducing waste.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

